The All Progressives Congress (APC) Professional Council has begun house-to-house and town hall campaigns to promote the party’s programmes and ensure it wins the July 16 governorship election. Director-General of the Council Seyi Bamigbade said the council has appointed Chairman of Ife Central Local Government Area, Elugbaju Olayera, as leader of the house-to-house campaign team, and the council’s National Director for Youth and Students Affairs, Adebayo Adewale, as secretary. Bamigbade said the group came up with the initiative to contribute meaningfully to the re-election of Governor Adegboyega Oyetola.   10 dead, seven injured in Yobe crash     Acting Accountant-General replaced     I never asked Christians to buy guns, says Adeboye   According to him, the house-to-house voter education and sensitisation will run in all the local government areas to galvanise professionals’ participation in the electoral process. Bamgbade appealed to the appointees to see the assignment as a sacred duty, while reminding the people about Governor Oyetola’s achievements in the last three years. National Publicity Secretary of the Council Fatai Abiodun said the programme will help to educate and enlighten potential voters on the need to vote right. According to him, only the candidacy of Governor Oyetola can bring the needed change the state yearns for, and sustain the giant stride recorded by the administration.